            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>Shaped ostraca made from a wall of a BG open vessel are a common find on Berezan and at Olbia. Often these roundels
                    are not inscribed. The back of the ostracon shows part of an eye of the original painted decoration of an Attic eye-cup. It is possible that the choice
                of the potsherd for making the shaped ostracon was determined by the presence of this decoration: there is noticeable preference for fragments of 
                painted pottery for some shaped ostraca.</p>
            </div>
